==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cadmium
<hw>Cad"mi*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Cadmia</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A comparatively rare
element related to zinc, and occurring in some zinc ores. It is a white
metal, both ductile and malleable. Symbol Cd. Atomic weight 111.8. It
was discovered by Stromeyer in 1817, who named it from its association
with zinc or zinc ore.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cadmium yellow</b></col>, <cd>a compound of cadmium and
sulphur, of an intense yellow color, used as a pigment.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cadrans</ent>⟦br⟧
